# Backend (NestJS)

- API prefix: `api/v1`. Swagger at `/api/docs` (development only).
- Auth: JWT bearer (`JwtAuthGuard` global). Public routes use `@Public()`. Roles via `@Roles()`.
- Errors: throw `HttpException` with `{ message, code }` using codes from `common/constants/error-codes.ts`.
- Audit sensitive actions via injected `AuditService` (global module).
- Inventory stock lives in `products` + `inventory_receive`; do not query legacy `materials` unless adding a new module.
- CPK calls optional — gate on `CpkTokenService.getMcId()` before `resPuidRecv` / `updatePuidStatus`.
- MQTT/Redis: log connection failures once; use fallbacks. Do not spam reconnect logs.
- PHP bcrypt: normalize `$2y$` → `$2a$` before `bcrypt.compare` in auth.
- After edits: `cd backend && npm run build && npm test`.
